#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:1.1.0"
msgid "81. Dubbalasikkhāpada"
msgstr ""
"<hgroup><h1 id=\"Bu-Pc.81\">Monks’ Confession 81: the training rule on what "
"is worn out</h1></hgroup>"

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.154
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"nidana\">Origin story</h2><p><a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.154\""
">Vin.4.154</a><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.81.1\">Bu-Pc.81.1</a><a class"
"=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.64\">BD.3.64</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1420</a>At one "
"time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel "
"sanctuary."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:1.1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā dabbo mallaputto saṃghassa senāsanañca "
"paññapeti bhattāni ca uddisati."
msgstr ""
"At that time Venerable Dabba the Mallian, who was the assigner of dwellings "
"and the designator of meals,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:1.1.3"
msgid "So cāyasmā dubbalacīvaro hoti."
msgstr "had a robe that was worn out."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:1.1.4"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena saṃghassa ekaṃ cīvaraṃ uppannaṃ hoti."
msgstr "Just then the Order had obtained robe-cloth,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:1.1.5"
msgid "Atha kho saṃgho taṃ cīvaraṃ āyasmato dabbassa mallaputtassa adāsi."
msgstr "and it gave it to Dabba."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:1.1.6"
msgid "Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "The monks from the group of six complained and criticized it,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:1.1.7"
msgid "“yathāsanthutaṃ bhikkhū saṃghikaṃ lābhaṃ pariṇāmentī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The monks are diverting the Order’s requisites according to friendship.”</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:1.1.8"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1421</a>The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:1.1.9"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:1.1.10"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū samaggena saṃghena cīvaraṃ datvā pacchā "
"khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjissantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six give out robe-cloth together with a "
"complete Order and then criticize it afterwards?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:1.1.11"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, samaggena saṃghena cīvaraṃ datvā pacchā "
"khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:1.1.12"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:1.1.13"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:1.1.14"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, samaggena saṃghena cīvaraṃ datvā pacchā "
"khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjissatha."
msgstr ""
"Foolish men, how can you give out robe-cloth together with a complete Order "
"and then criticize it afterwards?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:1.1.15"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ, vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:1.1.16"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="rule">
#. REF: sc3
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:1.1.17"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu samaggena saṃghena cīvaraṃ datvā pacchā khīyanadhammaṃ "
"āpajjeyya ‘yathāsanthutaṃ bhikkhū saṃghikaṃ lābhaṃ pariṇāmentī’ti, "
"pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pannatti\">Final ruling</h2><p class=\"rule\"><a class=\"pts-vp-en\""
" id=\"BD.3.65\">BD.3.65</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1422</a>‘If a monk gives out "
"robe-cloth together with a complete Order and then criticizes it afterwards, "
"saying, “The monks are giving out the Order’s requisites according to "
"friendship,” he commits an offense entailing confession.’”</p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pada\">Definitions</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.81.2\""
"></a><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.81.2.1\">Bu-Pc.81.2.1</a><a class=\"wt-"
"pa\">1423</a><term>A</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>whoever …</gloss>"

#. HTML: </b><b class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "<term>Monk</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>…"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr ""
"The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through "
"a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this "
"case.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.1.6"
msgid "Samaggo nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1424</a><term>A complete Order</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.1.7"
msgid "saṃgho samānasaṃvāsako samānasīmāyaṃ ṭhito."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>belonging to the same community, staying within the same "
"boundary.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.1.8"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1425</a><term>Robe-cloth</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.1.9"
msgid "channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ vikappanupagaṃ pacchimaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>one of the six kinds of robe-cloth,<span class=\"note\">*<fn>The six "
"are linen, cotton, silk, wool, sunn hemp, and hemp; see "
"<ref>Mv.8.3.1</ref>.</fn></span> but not smaller than what can be "
"transferred.<span class=\"note\">*<fn>This means not smaller than 8 by 4 "
"standard (<i lang=\"pi\">sugata</i>) finger-breadths, or 16 by 8 cm; see "
"<ref>Kkh.94.4</ref> and BMC I, pp. 565-566.</fn></span></gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.1.10"
msgid "Datvāti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1426</a><term>Gives out</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.1.11"
msgid "sayaṃ datvā."
msgstr "<gloss>having given it himself.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.1.12"
msgid "Yathāsanthutaṃ nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1427</a><term>According to friendship</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.1.13"
msgid ""
"yathāmittatā yathāsandiṭṭhatā yathāsambhattatā yathāsamānupajjhāyakatā "
"yathāsamānācariyakatā."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>according to friendship, according to companionship, according to who "
"one is devoted to, according to having the same preceptor, according to "
"having the same teacher.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.1.14"
msgid "Saṃghikaṃ nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1428</a><term>The Order’s</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.1.15"
msgid "saṃghassa dinnaṃ hoti pariccattaṃ."
msgstr "<gloss>given to the Order, given up to the Order.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.1.16"
msgid "Lābho nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1429</a><term>Requisites</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.1.17"
msgid ""
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā, antamaso "
"cuṇṇapiṇḍopi, dantakaṭṭhampi, dasikasuttampi."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>robe-cloth, almsfood, a dwelling, and medicines; even bath powder, a "
"toothbrush, or a piece of string.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc11, pts-vp-pli4.155
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.1.18"
msgid "Pacchā khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjeyyāti"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.155\">Vin.4.155</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1430</a><term>Criticizes it afterwards</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.1.19"
msgid ""
"upasampannassa saṃghena sammatassa senāsanapaññāpakassa vā bhattuddesakassa "
"vā yāgubhājakassa vā phalabhājakassa vā khajjabhājakassa vā "
"appamattakavissajjakassa vā cīvaraṃ dinne khiyyati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>when robe-cloth has been given to someone who is fully ordained and "
"who is the assigner of dwellings or the designator of meals or the "
"distributor of rice-porridge or the distributor of fruit or the distributor "
"of <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.66\">BD.3.66</a> non-staple food<span "
"class=\"note\">*<fn><i lang=\"pi\">Khajjaka</i>. According to "
"<ref>Sp.4.893.16</ref> (commenting on the <i lang=\"pi\">sekhiya</i> rules) "
"this refers to all non-staple foods: <i lang=\"pi\">ettha mūlakhādanīyādi "
"sabbaṃ gahetabbaṃ</i>, “Here the non-staple foods which are roots, etc., may "
"all be taken.”</fn></span> or the distributor of minor requisites, and he "
"has been agreed upon by the Order as such, then if a monk criticizes it, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p>
#. REF: sc12
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.2.1"
msgid ""
"Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññī cīvaraṃ dinne khiyyati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"cakka\">Permutations</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.81.2\""
"></a><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.81.2.2\">Bu-Pc.81.2.2</a><a class=\"wt-"
"pa\">1431</a>If it is a legitimate procedure, and he perceives it as "
"legitimate, and he criticizes it when robe-cloth has been given, he commits "
"an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.2.2"
msgid "Dhammakamme vematiko cīvaraṃ dinne khiyyati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a legitimate procedure, but he is unsure if it is, and he "
"criticizes it when robe-cloth has been given, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.2.3"
msgid ""
"Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññī cīvaraṃ dinne khiyyati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is a legitimate procedure, but he perceives it as illegitimate, and he "
"criticizes it when robe-cloth has been given, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.2.4"
msgid "Aññaṃ parikkhāraṃ dinne khiyyati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1432</a>If he criticizes it when another requisite has "
"been given, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.2.5"
msgid ""
"Upasampannassa saṃghena asammatassa senāsanapaññāpakassa vā bhattuddesakassa "
"vā yāgubhājakassa vā phalabhājakassa vā khajjabhājakassa vā "
"appamattakavissajjakassa vā cīvaraṃ vā aññaṃ vā parikkhāraṃ dinne khiyyati, "
"āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"When someone who is fully ordained is the assigner of dwellings or the "
"designator of meals or the distributor of rice-porridge or the distributor "
"of fruit or the distributor of non-staple food or the distributor of minor "
"requisites, but he has not been agreed upon by the Order as such, and a monk "
"criticizes it when robe-cloth or another requisite has been given to him, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.2.6"
msgid ""
"Anupasampannassa saṃghena sammatassa vā asammatassa vā senāsanapaññāpakassa "
"vā bhattuddesakassa vā yāgubhājakassa vā phalabhājakassa vā khajjabhājakassa "
"vā appamattakavissajjakassa vā cīvaraṃ vā aññaṃ vā parikkhāraṃ dinne "
"khiyyati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"When someone who is not fully ordained is the assigner of dwellings or the "
"designator of meals or the distributor of rice-porridge or the distributor "
"of fruit or the distributor of non-staple food or the distributor of minor "
"requisites, whether he has been agreed upon by the Order as such or not, and "
"a monk criticizes it when robe-cloth or another requisite has been given to "
"him, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.2.7"
msgid "Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p>If it is an illegitimate procedure, but he perceives it as legitimate, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.2.8"
msgid "Adhammakamme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.2.9"
msgid "Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure, and he perceives it as illegitimate, "
"there is no offense.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"anapatti\">Non-offenses</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.81.2."
"3\">Bu-Pc.81.2.3</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1433</a>There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.3.2"
msgid ""
"pakatiyā chandā dosā mohā bhayā karontaṃ “kvattho tassa dinnena laddhāpi "
"vinipātessati na sammā upanessatī”ti khiyyati, ummattakassa, ādikammikassāti."
msgstr ""
"if he criticizes one who normally acts from desire, ill-will, confusion, or "
"fear, saying, “What’s the point of giving it to him—he’ll ruin it and not "
"make use of it in an appropriate way;” if he is insane; if he is the first "
"offender.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc81:2.3.3"
msgid "Dubbalasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ ekādasamaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<hr><p class=\"endsutta\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1434</a>The eleventh rule, the "
"training rule on what is worn out, is finished.</p>"
